==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mirliton
<hw>Mir"li*ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of musical toy into which one sings, hums, or
speaks, producing a coarse, reedy sound. It is also called a
<altname>kazoo</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>Trilby singing ⟦ldquo⟧Ben Bolt⟦rdquo⟧ into a <qex>mirliton</qex>
was a thing to be remembered, whether one would or no!</q> <rj><qau>Du
Maurier.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>same as <er>chayote{2}</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mirounga</ent>⟦br⟧
